overview: The film portrays two of the most important producers of a movement born in the early 2000s, as well as the testimonies of some of its signatures dancers. In addition, it shows the initiative of Abstractor Collective to rescue and export the authenticity of a catchy rhythm that begins to count amongst its followers important producers and artist of the international electronic scene.
tagline: A short documentary about Changa Tuki, an underground electronic sound born in the slums of the city of Caracas, Venezuela.
title: Who Wants Tuki?
